The bulk densities of the thoria powders were found to lie between 1 and 1.2Mgm−3 (Table 1
                         and Fig. 1
                        ). These values are comparable with those pertaining to pure [11] and doped thoria [14] reported in earlier investigations. Even though the bulk density does not show any dependence on the dopant concentration, a marginal increase in the same is observed with the concentration of calcia in the host matrix while the magnesia doped powders did not exhibit such behaviour. The values of specific surface area of these powders (Table 1 and Fig. 2
                        ) were not significantly affected by the concentration of the dopant. This observation is similar to the trend observed in Ref. [11] and is in contrast to the results reported in an earlier study on thoria doped with cations of group VB [7].
